POLAND DAYBOOK: April PMI, Cabinet on Budget, Exchange Auction

-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 
2011-05-04T05:39:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/poland-daybook-april-pmi-cabinet-on-budget-exchange-auction.html
Poland ’s purchasing managers’ index, a
gauge of manufacturing, may have accelerated for a second
straight month in April to 55 points, supporting expectations
for a rate increase next week, according to the median estimate
of 55 economists surveyed by Bloomberg. HSBC Holdings Plc will
publish the survey by Markit Economics at 9 a.m.  ALL TIMES CET  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Bank Gospodarki Zywnosciowej SA publishes IPO prospectus and
holds a news briefing at 9:30 a.m.
* Ukraine’s Industrial Milk Company debuts on the  Warsaw Stock
Exchange , which will unveil a new index of Ukrainian companies
at an 11 a.m. briefing with bourse President Ludwik Sobolewski.
* The Finance Ministry will sell bonds maturing in 2015 and 2020
at an exchange offer auction. Results at 12:30 p.m.  GOVERNMENT
* Prime Minister Donald Tusk will discuss the 2012 draft budget
with ministers in preparation for a cabinet meeting tomorrow to
approve the measure.  EQUITY MOVERS:
*  Telekomunikacja Polska SA (TPS)  should receive a ruling from
Poland’s telecommunications watchdog in coming days on a
possible refund of 800 million zloty ($300 million), Parkiet
reported, without citing anyone.
* A group composed of Biosyntec, a French biotechnology company
that makes cigarette filters, and Amsterdam-based fuel trader
Trafigura Beheer B.V. was among those placing bids on April 29
for the Polish government’s 53 percent stake in  Grupa Lotos SA (LTS) ,
the country’s second-largest oil refiner, Puls Biznesu reported
today, quoting a person familiar with the matter.
*  Netia SA (NET) , Poland’s No. 2 fixed-line phone company, private
equity fund Bridgepoint, as well as Polish companies  Hawe SA (HWE)  and
 MNI SA (MNI)  have been invited to carry out due diligence on  KGHM
Polska Miedz SA (KGH) ’s Dialog phone unit, Puls Biznesu said, without
citing anyone.  MARKETS:
* The benchmark WIG20 stock index rose 0.2 percent to 2,919.81
on May 2.
* The MSCI Emerging Markets Index fell 1.7 percent.
* The zloty weakened to 3.9441 per euro from 3.9388 at 7:33 a.m.
* The yield on government debt maturing in October 2020 rose to
6.146 percent from 6.143 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David McQuaid in Warsaw 
 dmcquaid1@bloomberg.net  